headline.main: ALLIED AIRMEN DOWN 14 FOES IN TIMOR RAID; MacArthur Sees New Threat to Australia Developing

lead_paragraph: AT UNITED NATIONS HEADQUARTERS, Australia, Monday, March 1 (U.P.) -- Allied planes, battering at Timor Island southwest of New Guinea, destroyed fourteen Japanese planes and probably destroyed nine more at Kupang yesterday, United Nations Headquarters announced today.
abstract: Allied planes raid Penfoel airdrome, Kupang, Timor; destroy 14, possibly 23, Jap planes; Allied land patrols repel foe, Waipaining-Waipali and Wau areas, New Guinea; Jap strength reptd growing north of Australia
